fighter-tree-skill-body-training-1 = Body Training I
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-1-desc = The first layer of real training is simple: move more, tire less, and make your body obey before technique ever enters the picture.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-1 = Move 5% faster.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-2 = Body Training II
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-2-desc = Repetition hardens the body against ordinary impact until taking a hit stops being a surprise and starts being part of training.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-2 = Take 5% less physical damage.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-3 = Body Training III
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-3-desc = Once your frame starts cooperating, every clean punch carries more weight even before you know any advanced form.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-3 = Deal 5% more unarmed damage.

fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-1 = Prodigy I
fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-1-desc = During this stage of training, prove that your body is already outgrowing ordinary drills by breaking a space carp with at least five clean unarmed strikes before the kill.
fighter-tree-effect-prodigy-speed = Gain 10% passive movement speed.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-4 = Body Training IV
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-4-desc = You learn how to breathe, brace, and recover without wasting precious effort on every motion.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-4 = Spend 5% less stamina on exertion.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-5 = Body Training V
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-5-desc = Endless striking drills teach your hands to cycle faster without breaking structure.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-5 = Attack 5% faster with fists and fist-style glove weapons.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-6 = Body Training VI
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-6-desc = Constant contact work strengthens your body and teaches it to hit harder through repetition alone.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-6 = Deal 5% more unarmed damage.

fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-2 = Prodigy II
fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-2-desc = Show that your conditioning has outpaced common limits by tearing down a space bear with at least seven valid unarmed strikes during this training stage.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-7 = Body Training VII
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-7-desc = More rounds, more sprints, more movement. Your body starts carrying you faster without asking permission.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-7 = Move 5% faster.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-8 = Body Training VIII
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-8-desc = Bruises, strain, and pressure stop feeling exceptional. Your frame gets used to enduring them.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-8 = Take 5% less physical damage.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-9 = Body Training IX
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-9-desc = You are still not learning secret techniques, but your basic strikes are becoming undeniably harder to ignore.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-9 = Deal 5% more unarmed damage.

fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-3 = Prodigy III
fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-3-desc = Touch the edge of something greater by landing five valid unarmed strikes on the space dragon before your ordinary training stage passes you by.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-10 = Body Training X
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-10-desc = Better conditioning means less wasted effort, and less wasted effort means you can keep pushing longer.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-10 = Spend 5% less stamina on exertion.

fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-4 = Prodigy IV
fighter-tree-skill-prodigy-4-desc = After awakening this prodigy branch, finish the space dragon with your own unarmed strength and prove that your body has stepped beyond normal limits.

fighter-tree-skill-body-training-11 = Body Training XI
fighter-tree-skill-body-training-11-desc = Repetition turns panic into rhythm, and rhythm lets your fists cycle faster without losing form.
fighter-tree-effect-body-training-11 = Attack 5% faster with fists and fist-style glove weapons.

fighter-tree-skill-insight = Insight
fighter-tree-skill-insight-desc = Your body finally understands what all the repetition was building toward. You are ready to step beyond ordinary training.
fighter-tree-effect-insight = Deal 5% more unarmed damage.

fighter-tree-skill-martial-artist-path = Martial Artist Path
fighter-tree-skill-martial-artist-path-desc = Commit to technique, discipline, and learning a defined combat school.
fighter-tree-effect-martial-artist-path = Locks you into the Martial Artist route.

fighter-tree-skill-ki-warrior-path = Ki Warrior Path
fighter-tree-skill-ki-warrior-path-desc = Commit to patient body-and-energy training that leads toward the Dragon Ball paths ahead.
fighter-tree-effect-ki-warrior-path = Locks you into the Ki Warrior route and makes your body reject protective gear.

fighter-tree-skill-technique-mind = Technique Mind
fighter-tree-skill-technique-mind-desc = You start thinking less like a brawler and more like a trained martial artist.
fighter-tree-effect-technique-mind = Gain a small passive melee bonus.

fighter-tree-skill-center-line = Center Line
fighter-tree-skill-center-line-desc = Better structure and positioning make every exchange cleaner.
fighter-tree-effect-center-line = Gain a tiny passive movement speed bonus.

fighter-tree-skill-combat-rhythm = Combat Rhythm
fighter-tree-skill-combat-rhythm-desc = You settle into a fighting tempo that makes advanced styles possible.
fighter-tree-effect-combat-rhythm = Gain a small passive physical resistance bonus.

fighter-tree-skill-corporate-judo = Corporate Judo
fighter-tree-skill-corporate-judo-desc = Learn the corporate art of control, throws, and leverage.
fighter-tree-effect-corporate-judo = Permanently unlocks Corporate Judo. Choosing it closes the other martial arts.

fighter-tree-skill-capoeira = Capoeira
fighter-tree-skill-capoeira-desc = Learn a flowing, evasive style that turns movement into offense.
fighter-tree-effect-capoeira = Permanently unlocks Capoeira. Choosing it closes the other martial arts.

fighter-tree-skill-kung-fu-dragon = Kung Fu Dragon
fighter-tree-skill-kung-fu-dragon-desc = Follow the dragon style and train into a martial art built on relentless momentum.
fighter-tree-effect-kung-fu-dragon = Permanently unlocks Kung Fu Dragon. Choosing it closes the other martial arts.

fighter-tree-skill-close-quarters-combat = Close Quarters Combat
fighter-tree-skill-close-quarters-combat-desc = Learn brutal practical combat focused on ending a fight fast.
fighter-tree-effect-close-quarters-combat = Permanently unlocks CQC. Choosing it closes the other martial arts.

fighter-tree-skill-sleeping-carp = Sleeping Carp
fighter-tree-skill-sleeping-carp-desc = The forbidden school. It is only available to a boxer who has truly crossed into the syndicate traitor path.
fighter-tree-effect-sleeping-carp = Permanently unlocks Sleeping Carp, but only while you have the Traitor role. Choosing it closes the other martial arts.

fighter-tree-skill-breathing-training-1 = Breathing Training I
fighter-tree-skill-breathing-training-1-desc = The first step is simple breath discipline. Every motion wastes a little less effort when your breathing stays under control.
fighter-tree-effect-breathing-training-1 = Spend 3% less stamina on exertion.

fighter-tree-skill-ki-body-training-1 = Body Training I
fighter-tree-skill-ki-body-training-1-desc = Basic conditioning continues, but now every impact is treated as part of learning how the body should carry energy.
fighter-tree-effect-ki-body-training-1 = Take 3% less physical damage.

fighter-tree-skill-focus-training-1 = Focus Training I
fighter-tree-skill-focus-training-1-desc = Your attention stops drifting during exchanges, letting your fists cycle a little faster without losing form.
fighter-tree-effect-focus-training-1 = Attack 3% faster with fists and fist-style glove weapons.

fighter-tree-skill-breathing-training-2 = Breathing Training II
fighter-tree-skill-breathing-training-2-desc = Breath and footwork begin syncing together, making your movement lighter without any dramatic breakthrough.
fighter-tree-effect-breathing-training-2 = Move 3% faster.

fighter-tree-skill-ki-body-training-2 = Body Training II
fighter-tree-skill-ki-body-training-2-desc = More rounds and more repetition steadily add weight behind your basic strikes.
fighter-tree-effect-ki-body-training-2 = Deal 3% more unarmed damage.

fighter-tree-skill-focus-training-2 = Focus Training II
fighter-tree-skill-focus-training-2-desc = Better control means less wasted strain, letting you keep pressure without bleeding energy away.
fighter-tree-effect-focus-training-2 = Spend 5% less stamina on exertion.

fighter-tree-skill-breathing-training-3 = Breathing Training III
fighter-tree-skill-breathing-training-3-desc = Breathing under pressure stops being a drill and becomes a habit, helping your body endure harder contact.
fighter-tree-effect-breathing-training-3 = Take 5% less physical damage.

fighter-tree-skill-ki-body-training-3 = Body Training III
fighter-tree-skill-ki-body-training-3-desc = Your hands are trained through enough repetition that even simple combinations come out faster than before.
fighter-tree-effect-ki-body-training-3 = Attack 5% faster with fists and fist-style glove weapons.

fighter-tree-skill-focus-training-3 = Focus Training III
fighter-tree-skill-focus-training-3-desc = Stillness of mind makes your movement cleaner and quicker without wasting power on panic.
fighter-tree-effect-focus-training-3 = Move 5% faster.

fighter-tree-skill-ki-training = Ki Training
fighter-tree-skill-ki-training-desc = Your body is finally used to carrying controlled internal pressure. You are ready to push into something greater.
